lzh_formatted:
  title: 依靈通舊令
  author: 朴誾
  language: lzh
  text: 月照浪不動。夜凉風肅然。高談元出世。佳句欲侵仙。孤舟唯所止。百丈更誰牽。欲記今霄樂。秋風壬戌年。
korean:
  title: 의 영통 구령
  author: 박은
  language: kor
  text: |-
    달은 비치는데 물결은 고요하고
    밤은 시원한데 바람은 쓸쓸하다
    고상한 이야기는 원래 세상에 뛰어나고
    아름다운 글귀는 신선을 범하려네
    외로운 배는 오직 머물대로인데
    백장 닻줄 다시 누가 끌 것인가
    오늘 밤 즐거움을 기록하려 하노니
    가을 바람이 부는 임술년이다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1420_010_0820&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Following the Spirit's Harmony—An Old Decree
  author: Park Eun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The moon shines, yet the waters lie still,
    The night cools, and the wind grows desolate.
    Lofty discourse transcends the world of dust,
    Fine verses dare approach the realm of immortals.
    My lonely boat rests where it will,
    A hundred fathoms of rope—who will draw it further?
    I wish to capture tonight's joy,
    In this autumn wind of the Imsu year.
  footnotes:
    - The 'Imsu year' (임술년) refers to a specific year in the traditional East Asian sexagenary cycle, likely indicating a particular moment of composition that would have been significant to the author's contemporaries.
    - The 'hundred fathoms' (백장) represents a great depth, suggesting both the vastness of the waters and, metaphorically, the profound nature of the moment being experienced.
